! Hotkey

|!Key |!Action |
|''Ctrl-Space'' |Open the palette |
|''Up / Down'' |Move selection within the current stage |
|''Tab'' |Drill into the selected item — push a new stage |
|''Enter'' |Fire the selected item and close the palette |
|''Shift-Enter'' |Fire the selected item but keep the palette open (current stage refreshes to reflect any changes) |
|''Esc'' |Pop one stage; if at root, close the palette |
|''Shift-Tab'' |Same as Esc — pop one stage, close at root |
|''Click'' on a result row |Same as selecting + Enter |
|''Click'' on a breadcrumb segment |Pop back to that stage |

The hotkey is configured at `$:/config/shortcuts/rimir-cascade-palette-open`.

! Tags

|!Tag |!Purpose |
|`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/entry` |Root-stage menu item |
|`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/action` |Per-entity-type action menu item |

! Fields

|!Field |!Type |!Where |!Purpose |
|`ca-name` |string |entry, action |Display name in the row |
|`ca-hint` |string |entry, action |Subtitle / right-aligned hint |
|`ca-icon` |string |entry, action |Single character or emoji prefix |
|`ca-order` |number |entry, action |Sort key (lower = higher in list, default 100) |
|`ca-kind` |`leaf`\|`drill` |entry, action |Leaf fires actions, drill pushes next stage |
|`ca-actions` |wikitext |leaf items |Fired on Enter |
|`ca-entity-type` |string\|`*` |action |Entity type this action applies to, or `*` for global |
|`ca-default` |`yes`\|empty |action |Marks the "Enter on entity result" default action |
|`ca-next-scope` |filter |drill items |Filter expression for the new stage's items |
|`ca-next-title` |string |drill items |Title shown in breadcrumb for the new stage |
|`ca-next-entity-type` |string |drill items |Sets the next stage's entity type (enables action-menu drilling on Tab) |
|`ca-next-default-action` |wikitext |drill items |Fired on Enter in the next stage when no entity default exists |
|`ca-group` |string |entry, action |Override the visual cluster label. Defaults to the contributing plugin's `name`. Headers are suppressed when only one cluster is present in a stage. |
|`ca-visibility-filter` |filter |entry |If present and returns no results, the entry is hidden from the root menu |

! Settings

|!Tiddler |!Default |!Effect |
|`$:/config/shortcuts/rimir-cascade-palette-open` |`ctrl+space` |Hotkey to open the palette |
|`$:/config/rimir/cascade-palette/max-results` |`30` |Cap on items shown per stage |

! JavaScript message

|!Message |!Dispatched from |!Handled by |
|`rimir-cascade-palette-open` |Keyboard shortcut binding or any wikitext via `$action-sendmessage` |The widget's listener on `$tw.rootWidget` |

! Filter substitution variables

|!Variable |!Available in |!Value |
|`<<query>>` |scope, action |Current input text |
|`<<picked>>` |action |Title of the item just picked |
|`<<parent-picked>>` |scope, action |Title picked in the parent stage |
|`<<stage-N-picked>>` |scope, action |Title picked at stage index N (root = 0) |

! Mount point

The widget is injected into `document.body` at boot via the startup module `widgets/cascade-palette-startup.js`. Mount-point ID: `rimir-cascade-palette-mount`. To inspect: `document.getElementById("rimir-cascade-palette-mount")`.

! Console diagnostics

The widget logs at boot:

* `[cascade-palette] startup mount complete — widget in document.body` — startup module ran successfully
* `[cascade-palette] widget render() — mounting` — widget's render method ran
* `[cascade-palette] hotkey listener registered on rootWidget` — message handler wired
* `[cascade-palette] open message received` — fires every time the palette opens (via hotkey or programmatic dispatch)
* `[cascade-palette] action invocation failed: ...` — fires when `invokeViaNavigator()` throws (most likely cause: filter or wikitext error in `ca-actions` / `ca-next-scope` / `ca-next-default-action`)
